# Core Rules

## What this file is for
Repository-wide coding and collaboration rules that apply to all files.

## When to read/use this
Use these rules for every change in this repository.

## Core Principles
- Prefer small, focused changes.
- Keep behavior explicit and readable.
- Preserve existing patterns unless a documented refactor is planned.

## Code Style
- Follow existing style in each area of the repo.
- Use clear naming and avoid unnecessary abstraction.

## File Organization
- Keep files in their appropriate domain directories.
- Place long-term docs under `docs/` and temporary notes under `temp-doc/`.

## Naming Conventions
- Use descriptive names for files, folders, and symbols.
- Keep naming consistent with nearby code.
